KW  - Artificial intelligence
KW  - Machine learning
KW  - Deep learning
KW  - Neural network
KW  - Stochastic gradient
KW  - Dynamic models
KW  - Model reduction
KW  - Dynamic programming
KW  - Bellman equation
KW  - Euler equation
KW  - Value functio
AB  - We introduce a unified deep learning method that solves dynamic economic models by casting them into nonlinear regression equations. We derive such equations for three fundamental objects of economic dynamics – lifetime reward functions, Bellman equations and Euler equations. We estimate the decision functions on simulated data using a stochastic gradient descent method. We introduce an all-in-one integration operator that facilitates approximation of high-dimensional integrals. We use neural networks to perform model reduction and to handle multicollinearity. Our deep learning method is tractable in large-scale problems, e.g., Krusell and Smith (1998). We provide a TensorFlow code that accommodates a variety of applications.
